        // ── Overview (Article) ───────────────────────────────────────────
        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
        {
            Title = "Shop Floor Display Overview",
            Slug = "shop-floor-overview",
            Summary = "What the shop floor display is, how kiosk mode works, scan-based authentication, worker cards, and job actions.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Article,
            EstimatedMinutes = 5,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 1,
            AppRoutes = """["/display/shop-floor"]""",
            Tags = """["shop-floor","kiosk","display","clock"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Shop Floor Display Overview\n\nThe Shop Floor Display is a full-screen kiosk built for the production floor. It's a touch-friendly, always-on screen where workers can clock in and out, see their jobs, start and stop timers, mark jobs complete, receive goods, and ship orders — all without opening the main app.\n\n### Kiosk Mode\n\nThe display runs on its own — no sidebar, no toolbar, no menus. The whole screen is the shop floor. It's meant to run on a dedicated monitor or tablet mounted on the floor. To leave the kiosk, use Exit kiosk in the top corner, which returns to the login screen.\n\nThe screen refreshes on its own every few seconds so worker status and jobs stay current. A live clock sits in the header. Your light/dark and text-size choices are remembered, even after the browser restarts.\n\n### Two Versions\n\nThere are two shop floor screens:\n- **The main display** — a grid of worker cards, an unassigned-jobs section, upcoming events, and the full set of actions (clock, timers, receiving, shipping).\n- **The clock kiosk** — a simpler clock-in/clock-out station with terminal setup, a team filter, and a scan-first flow.\n\nThe main display quietly listens for scans anywhere on the screen; the clock kiosk uses one focused scan box.\n\n### Signing In\n\nThe display uses a sign-in for one action at a time — there's no lasting login. You sign in, do your action, and you're signed out automatically. There are two ways:\n\n1. **Scan + PIN:** Scan your badge or barcode. If it matches a worker, a PIN box appears. Type your number PIN (at least 4 digits) and submit. Your actions open.\n\n2. **Tap card + password:** Tap your name card on the grid. A password box appears (your full password, not a PIN). Once it checks out, your actions open.\n\nTimeouts close stale boxes on their own: the PIN box after about 20 seconds, the job picker after about 15, and the action screen after about 30 seconds of no taps.\n\n### Worker Card Grid\n\nThe main screen shows everyone as a card. Each card has:\n- A colored edge showing clock status: green for working, yellow for break or lunch, gray for clocked out.\n- The worker's initials in a colored badge.\n- Their name and current status.\n- How long they've been in that status, counting up every second.\n- Their jobs (up to 4, with a '+N more' note), each with the job number, title, a colored stage dot, and a timer mark when its clock is running.\n\nTap a card to sign in. You can also drag an unassigned job onto a card to assign it.\n\n### Job Actions\n\nOnce you're signed in, you see your jobs with buttons:\n- **Start Timer** — begins tracking your time on the job.\n- **Stop Timer** — stops the running timer.\n- **Mark Complete** — moves the job to the next stage and records that it's done.\n\nBelow the jobs are **clock buttons** that change based on what you're doing now — Clock In, Clock Out, Break, Lunch, and any custom ones your site sets up.\n\n### Receiving and Shipping\n\nDock actions appear after you sign in, depending on your role:\n- **Receive Goods** — for Admins, Managers, Office Managers, Engineers, and Production Workers. Shows open purchase orders still due, plus/minus quantity buttons, an optional bin to put things in, and a Receive All button.\n- **Ship Goods** — for Admins, Managers, and Office Managers. Shows pending and packed shipments, the shipment's carrier and tracking, a Print Packing Slip button, and a Mark Shipped button.\n\n### Which Stages Show Here\n\nNot every stage shows on the shop floor. Each stage can be marked to appear here, and only marked stages put their jobs on the floor. This keeps office-only stages like quoting, invoicing, and payment out of the way.\n\n### Unassigned Jobs and Drag-and-Drop\n\nJobs with nobody assigned appear in their own section below the worker grid. Each shows its number, title, stage, a colored stage dot, and priority. Drag one onto a worker card to assign it. And if you clock in with no jobs, a job picker opens on its own so you can pick one.\n\n### Upcoming Events\n\nThe display also shows upcoming events — meetings, training, and safety sessions. Each shows an icon for its type, the title, start time, location, and a 'Required' tag when it applies.\n\n### Kiosk Settings\n\nThe header has:\n- **Text size** — bigger and smaller buttons with five steps. Your choice is remembered.\n- **Light/dark switch** — flips between light and dark. Your choice is remembered.\n- **Live clock** — shows the current time, ticking every second.\n- **Search box** — type a couple of letters to look up jobs, parts, and more.\n\n### Scan to Move Inventory\n\nScanning isn't only for clocking in. Scan a **part barcode** and the same action screen from the Inventory Scan page opens right here, offering the actions that fit that part — such as Move, Count, Receive, and Ship. Scan a **storage-bin barcode** and you get a list of everything in that bin — item, lot, and quantity — so you can work on any item in it. See the Inventory Scan Station article for the full set of actions and multi-scan.\n\n### Undo a Recent Scan\n\nMistakes happen — a part moved to the wrong bin, a count typed in wrong. The display has a **Recent Scan Actions** panel that lists scans from the last **6 hours**. Each entry shows the time, who did it, the action, quantity, part, and where it moved from and to. Press **Reverse** and a **PIN box** appears; a good PIN undoes the movement and marks the entry 'Reversed'. It's a checked correction, not a silent undo, and an already-undone entry can't be undone again.\n\n### Daily Scan Log\n\nFor the full history, the **Daily Scan Log** (its own page, or a panel) is a read-only list of every scan for a chosen day. Filter by **date** and by **action** (Move, Count, Receive, Ship, Issue), and a summary line tallies the day, like '12 scans today — 4 moves, 2 receives'. Undone scans show a red 'Reversed' tag. Where the undo panel is the quick 6-hour window, the Daily Scan Log is the lasting record.","sections":[]}"""
